name: v0.8.4
body:
- Add `Ref.toJS` for a reference to a pure JS component that has its own facade type.
- Add a `ref` param to `ReactCssTransitionGroup`.
- Add `.propsDynamic` as a convenience for `.props` cast to `js.Dynamic`.
- Tag attributes can be arrays. Allows for multiple-selection in `<select>`.
- Upgrade Monocle to 1.1.1.

name: v0.8.2
body:
- Upgrade to Scala.JS 0.6.1.
- Upgrade dependencies to versions built with Scala.JS 0.6.1.
- Hide internal methods.

name: v0.7.2
body:
- Added `isMounted` to component scopes.
- Added `Addons.ReactCloneWithProps`.
- Dropped Scalaz 7.0 support. (Scalaz 7.1 still supported.)
- Upgrade Scala.JS to 0.6.0.

name: v0.7.1
body:
- Support custom tags, attributes and styles via `"string".react{Attr,Style,Tag}`.
- The `class` attribute now gets some special treatment in that it appends rather than overwrites.
  `<.div(^.cls := "a", ^.cls := "b")` is now the same as `<.div(^.cls := "a b")`.

name: v0.7.0
body:
Lots and lots of stuff.

See [CHANGELOG-0.7.md](https://github.com/japgolly/scalajs-react/blob/master/doc/CHANGELOG-0.7.md).

name: v0.6.0
body:
Now supports (and requires) React version 0.12.0.

Full release notes in [HISTORY.md](https://github.com/japgolly/scalajs-react/blob/master/HISTORY.md).

name: v0.5.4
body:
\* Added `nop` and `_nop` to `ReactS.Fix{,T}`.
- Added `T[A]` to `ReactS.Fix{,T}`.
- Added `ReactS.liftIO` (workaround for Intellij).
- Made `ReactS.>>` lazy.

name: v0.5.3
body:
- Deprecated and renamed `StateT.liftR` in favour of `liftS`.
- Workaround for Scala's type inference failing with `StateT.liftS` on functions.
  Instead of `f(_).liftS`, `f.liftS` is now available and is confirmed to work in `_runState`.

name: v0.5.1
body:
- Fixed Scalatags rejecting `VDom`.
- Added `ScalazReact.ReactS.setM`.
- Added `Listenable.install{IO,F}`, added `M[_]` to `Listenable.installS`.
- Added `LogLifecycle` which when applied to a component, logs during each lifecycle callback.

name: v0.4.1
body:
- Upgrade to scalatags 0.4.0.
- Component builder supports multiple callbacks.
- JS source maps point to Github.
